    "body": "Looks like a fairly simple change could be made to the lexer so it uses `char::is_whitespace` instead of limiting to `' ', '\\n', '\\t', '\\r'`. The only think I can think of is that the `is_whitespace` function in `lexer/mod.rs` has been around since before we had a better `is_whitespace` function and nobody has changed it since then.\n",
